Presented by @backcountry x @simmsfishing
~
Video: @prestonhoffman_ for @teamflylords

node.text: With living rooms across the country morphing into home gyms and workouts venturing into uncharted territory, we reached out to adaptive athlete, @nationalabilitycenter ambassador, and Backcountry partner Santiago Vega to see how he's staying in shape. Check out @svsanchago’s at-home workout routine for athletes of all abilities. #AdaptiveNation

Athletes Brooklyn Bell (@badgal_brooky) and Caroline Gleich (@carolinegleich) are no strangers to long days in the backcountry. They recently joined us at Backcountry HQ to talk about their must-have items for backcountry skiing. Watch the video, then visit our Explore blog to learn more about Caroline and Brooklyn and the gear they pack for a day on the hill.

node.title: What to Pack for a Day in the Backcountry

node.text:
“Surfing is hard. You won’t get it right away. But there will be so many glimpses of joy and addicting moments that you won’t want to give up.”

When Caley Vanular (@caleyvanular) isn’t riding waves on her board, powder on her other board, or globe-trotting with her boards, she’s dishing out gear picks and advice for the surf-curious. From wave-catching surfboards to warmth-catching wetsuits—get the lowdown on all things surf with Caley’s picks at the link in our bio.
